  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A gift for life: a sheep for a family in Eritrea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project was born from the necessity of improving the life conditions of the poorest families living in rural villages. Our local partner has operated in Eritrea since 1886, offering sanitary assistance, women empowerment, education, child protection and assistance to youths, aged and sick people and convicts. In order to improve the supply of food and the economic conditions of the population, the nuns distribute goats and sheeps, thus creating little domestic livestocks.</narrative>
  </description>
